UNIVERSITY LMS — COMPLETE DEVELOPMENT TASK LIST (SEQUENCE-WISE)
(Follow these steps one by one. This is your official development roadmap.)
PHASE 1 — PROJECT SETUP (ROOT LEVEL)

Create GitHub repository

Create root folder university-lms/

Create two sub-projects:

backend/ → Django REST Framework

frontend/ → Next.js (TypeScript)

Add root README.md

Setup .gitignore for Python, Node, Logs, ENV files

Configure project-level environment variables structure

Setup virtual environments

Setup basic project documentation folder (docs/)

PHASE 2 — BACKEND SETUP (Django + DRF)
A. Project Bootstrapping

Create Django project lms_crm/

Create apps folder apps/

Create apps for each module:

users

courses

assignments

exams

results

finance

notifications

attendance

timetable

library

Install required packages (Django, DRF, JWT auth, CORS, etc.)

Configure settings (DB, apps, middleware, authentication)

Setup URLs, ASGI, WSGI

PHASE 3 — BACKEND MODULE DEVELOPMENT (In Order)
A. USERS MODULE (Start Here)

Create User models (Student, Teacher, Admin, Roles)

Create serializers

Add JWT authentication

Create permissions

Create Auth APIs: Login, Signup, Logout

Add signals (create profile on user creation)

Add admin configuration

Add tests

B. COURSES MODULE

Create models: Course, Module, Lesson, Resources

Create serializers

Create permissions

Create views (CRUD, enroll, manage materials)

Add search & filters

Add tests

C. ASSIGNMENTS MODULE

Create models: Assignment, Submission, Grade

Create serializers

Create views (create assignment, submit)

Add grading logic

Add tests

D. EXAMS MODULE

Create models: Exam, QuestionBank, Schedule

Create serializers

Build exam views (start exam, auto-grade, MCQs)

Build exam scoring logic

Add test cases

E. RESULTS MODULE

Create models: GPA, Transcript, Result

Add serializers

Add publish result APIs

Add calculations (CGPA, semester GPA)

Write tests

F. FINANCE MODULE

Create models: Fees, Challans, Payments, Scholarships

Add fee generation logic

Add payment validation

Connect payment APIs (Stripe/EasyPaisa/JazzCash - optional)

Add tests

G. NOTIFICATIONS MODULE

Create models for email, SMS, in-app messages

Write reusable notification services

Build send notification API

Write tests

H. ATTENDANCE MODULE

Create attendance models

Add views for marking attendance

Create analytics summary (per subject, per month)

Add tests

I. TIMETABLE MODULE

Create timetable models

Add timetable CRUD APIs

Add student/teacher timetable views

Run tests

J. LIBRARY MODULE

Create models (Book, Issue, Return)

Create book search & filter APIs

Create issue/return logic

Add tests

PHASE 4 — GLOBAL BACKEND SETUP

Setup media handling (file uploads)

Setup static file handling

Add custom exceptions

Add custom utils folder

Setup logging (info + errors)

Configure CORS for frontend

Run full backend testing

Generate API documentation in /docs/API/

PHASE 5 — FRONTEND SETUP (Next.js + TypeScript)
Initial Setup

Initialize Next.js project

Configure TypeScript

Setup TailwindCSS

Setup folder structure (src/pages, src/components, etc.)

Create API service layer (services/api.ts)

Create global Auth Context

Setup protected routes

Setup Axios interceptor with JWT

